<section id="fs-idp3478192" class="critical-thinking">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm1176992">
<problem id="fs-idp3477792">
<para id="fs-idm28028640">A balanced federal budget and a balance of trade are secondary goals of macroeconomics, while growth in the standard of living (for example) is a primary goal. Why do you think that is so? </para></problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm106255872">
