<para id="fs-idp24713424">Macroeconomics is an aggregate of what happens at the microeconomic level. Would it be possible for what happens at the macro level to differ from how economic agents would react to some stimulus at the micro level? <emphasis effect="italics">Hint: </emphasis>Think about the behavior of crowds. </para>
</problem>
